
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `gnome-www-browser` yek browser-e web-e sade ast ke baraye system-haye Linux ke az GNOME estefade mikonand, tarahi shode. In browser kheili sabok ast va baraye didane safhe-haye web-e sade va asasi munasib ast. 

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--new-window`  --> 🆕 Baz kardane safheye jadid dar panjere jadid.
    🔹 `--version`   --> ℹ️  Namayeshe version-e browser.
    🔹 `<URL>`       --> 🌐 Baz kardane yek URL moshakhas dar browser.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-www-browser
    
    🔹 Baz kardane browser be soorate sade.

    $ gnome-www-browser https://www.example.com
    
    🔹 Baz kardane safheye example.com dar browser.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-www-browser --version
    
    🔹 Namayeshe version-e browser.  In command be shoma komak mikonad ta motmaen shavid ke shoma az akharin version estefade mikonid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `gnome-www-browser` is a simple web browser designed for Linux systems using GNOME. It is lightweight and suitable for viewing basic web pages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--new-window`  --> 🆕 Open the page in a new window.
    🔹 `--version`   --> ℹ️  Display the browser version.
    🔹 `<URL>`       --> 🌐 Open a specific URL in the browser.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-www-browser
    
    🔹 Open the browser in a basic way.

    $ gnome-www-browser https://www.example.com
    
    🔹 Open the example.com page in the browser.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-www-browser --version
    
    🔹 Display the browser version. This command helps you ensure that you are using the latest version.
